				Being able to lead and communicate effectively are core elements of life goals... including New Year's resolutions.  This program: "ONE Goal to a Better Life" will help you chart a path to your goal by using opportunities in Toastmasters. 
			</p>

			<p style='font-size:12pt'>
					<strong>Q:</strong> How? 
				<br/>
				<strong>A:</strong> You will apply Toastmasters' research-proven techniques to achieving goals. The simple process is: set a goal, commit to it, work on it, track it,  and get support from others. A section of this website will show you how to use Toastmaster objectives (link c) to reach your goal.
			</p>

			<p style='font-size:12pt'>
				<strong>Q:</strong> Really?
				<br/>
				<strong>A:</strong> Think about it - you have used these principles to move along in Toastmasters - whether you have achieved your CC or CL or are working toward your DTM.
			</p>

			<p style='font-size:12pt'>
				<strong>Q:</strong> What type of life goals does this encompass?
				<br/>
				<strong>A:</strong> Just about anything. Do you want to lose weight? Do you want to run a marathon? Do you want to have a better relationship - with your spouse, your parents, your children or your friends? Do you want to get a promotion at work? Do you want to run for public office? We - the D28 Toastmasters community - can help you achieve it.
				Or, you can apply the "ONE goal" strictly to your Toastmaster education objective. With that, you'll get extra support and encouragement in finishing your manuals and completing leadership projects. 
			</p>


